If you could give me some , yes please

1 . Make sure your energy max is high—that is , get at least > ! the Stardrop on L100 , the Stardrop from the fall holiday fair , buy one from Krobus and maybe the one from Old Master Cannoli or your spouse . ! < 2 . Bring lots of good food . That ’ s chocolate cakes , autumn ’ s bounties , maple bars , crab cakes , pink cakes , etc . It may also be worth your time to buy the energy thing from the clinic . Have these in your toolbar and know the keystrokes for them . 3 . Bombs ! Cherry bombs for the mummies and normal ones for breaking rocks . These are the only way to destroy mummies and they clear things a lot faster . 4 . Have a quality weapon that you ’ re good at using . Clubs and swords are my preference , but if a dagger works for you , go for it . You ’ ll want something better than the Obsidian Blade . Obviously , the > ! Galaxy weapons ! < are best . 5 . This is one of the most important : * * Wear the crabshell and slime charmer rings . * * ( Gil gives them to you for the crab and slime goals at the Guild . ) You can farm monsters for these in the Mines pretty easily . Bring a glowing ring along as well , in case you need to see . But the first two rings , esp . the slime one , will * save you . * 6 . Whenever you find iridium ore nodes , before you mine it , swing a weapon at it . This will reveal if it ’ s a crab or an actual piece of ore . If it is a crab , evaluate if you have the health and energy to fight it . They tend to drop crab cakes , which are great . +225 energy , +101 energy , and a defense and speed boost . So it may still be good to fight , but it ’ s best to know first . 7 . Bring some staircases for emergencies .

I just now realize , is it possible to get 420G at one day by only selling seaweed ?

I believe the answer to that is yes . I spend a lot of time fishing in stardew valley , so I ’ d say that the average time between casts without any boosts is about 1 ingame hour , maybe a little less . You ’ d need 21 seaweed to hit that 420g , and the chance of a seaweed spawn is about 1 in 5 . Therefore , you ’ d need about 105 casts to win . Also , each 10 min ingame is 7 real world seconds . Normally , if you got down to the docks with a beach totem and fished until you passed out , you ’ d get about 4 seaweed . However , we can do much better . If you got consistent bubble luck , we could multiply that 4 seaweed times 4 to get 16 . Wild bait reduces bite time by 5/8 , which we ’ ll just call 1/2 . This doubles our to total to get 32 . Plus , there is the dressed spinner , which reduces bite time by 7.5 seconds . This gives us an insanely fast bite time , it ’ s totally doable
Or you can just fish for several days and sell all the seaweed on one day .

I 've written about this before , reposting it here : -- - I think this is one of those cases where there 's an acceptable break from reality . It 's not realistic that you can date any of the marriage candidates regardless of the gender , but the game would n't be as appealing to a lot of people if it limited player choice like that . It 's very common that games allowing romances will limit themselves to 1 ( maybe 2 if you 're lucky ) gay option for each gender , which is realistic given the size of the cast and the frequency of gay people in real life , but it means that straight players get to choose who they want to date , while gay players do n't ( and oftentimes that character is bi anyway , so straight players can still choose the opposite sex 's gay option , while gay players only get the one option ) . In real life , there are certainly fewer gay people than straight people , but since there are so many people , the gay dating scene is n't , `` here 's the gay option , take it or leave it . '' In a cast the size of Stardew Valley , realism would dictate that there 's a high chance none of the marriage candidates would be gay . Because of the common game design choice to limit gay players to the designated gay option , if I know a game has romance options going in and allows players to choose their gender , I 've taken to looking up how the game handles same sex relationships , and if it 's just `` here 's your token gay option , take it or leave it , '' I usually end up playing as a female character just so I can still participate in that part of the game . By making all the characters effectively bi , gay male players get to make the same choices as straight female players , and straight male players get the same choices as gay female players , so both gay and straight players alike can enjoy the romance aspects of the game . For gay players , the way Stardew Valley handles the sexuality of the marriage candidates is a nice escape from the reality of real life dating : on top of the chance that the other person just is n't interested in you that straight people also have to deal with , there 's the added challenge that , because of the ratio of gay people to straight people , it is likely that most people you find attractive will turn out to be straight . If you 're straight , and you 've been attracted to a person you later learned was gay , the equivalent experience for a gay person is probably around at least 20 times more probable .

Stardew isn ’ t a dating sim so I don ’ t think it really matters if it ’ s true to “ real life ” or not . bus to comatose is the conspiracy that the first time you travel to the desert via the bus , you get into an accident , fall into a coma , and everything else that happens is imagined , hence why weird things start happening afterwards ( usually players unlock the desert around when less `` realistic '' events start occurring ) Gate bomb warp is a 1.3 bug where you could put a fence down on floor 120 of the mines , bomb it , and that would create a ladder which would take you to floor 1 of skull cavern SC wrong warp is a bug which afaik still exists where sometimes on SC treasure floors , you can click the wall and it will put up the normal mines elevator menu that you can use to travel to the mines 6AM festival exploit is if you travel into a festival area on the day of the festival at 6AM sharp , the game will not prevent you from entering ( normally it blocks you and says `` festival is being set up etc '' )
